Here are common Git commands to get you started with version control:

🔧 Basic Git Setup
bash
Copy
Edit
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
📁 Repository Initialization
bash
Copy
Edit
git init                   # Initialize a new Git repository
📄 Staging & Committing Files
bash
Copy
Edit
git status                # Show current status
git add filename          # Stage a specific file
git add .                 # Stage all files
git commit -m "Message"   # Commit staged changes
🌐 Working with Remote Repositories
bash
Copy
Edit
git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git  # Add remote
git push -u origin main                                 # Push to main branch
📥 Cloning and Pulling
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git   # Clone a repo
git pull                                     # Pull latest changes
🔄 Branching
bash
Copy
Edit
git branch                    # List branches
git branch new-branch         # Create new branch
git checkout new-branch       # Switch to a branch
git checkout -b new-branch    # Create + switch
🔁 Merging
bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout main
git merge new-branch
🧹 Undoing Changes
bash
Copy
Edit
git restore filename         # Discard local changes
git reset HEAD filename      # Unstage a file
git reset --hard             # Danger: resets all changes
